    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ok understood, makes sense. So what you would need here is be able to call `search.start()` when you are ready.\n\nMaybe you can already do so: use your own `<input>`, bind events on it (DOM regular events), create the searchBox widget out of it, when you reach one character, call `search.start()`\n",
