    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Maybe you can already do so: use your own <input>, bind events on it (DOM regular events), create the searchBox widget out of it, when you reach one character, call search.start()\n\nThat's fine, I'm already doing this for my implementation :wink:\n\nJust wondering if it was something we wanted _out of the box_ without too much hassle. I was expecting `.start()` to behave more like an initializer, not actually searching without user's input / interaction.\n",
